<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Chorizanthe</i> <i>rigida</i> and/or <i>Geraea</i> <i>canescens</i> is characteristically present in the herbaceous layer with <i>Allionia</i> <i>incarnata</i>, <i>Brassica</i> <i>tournefortii</i>, <i>Bromus</i> <i>rubens</i>, <i>Camissonia</i> spp., <i>Chaenactis</i> spp., <i>Chamaesyce</i> spp., <i>Chorizanthe</i> <i>brevicornu</i>, <i>Cryptantha</i> spp., <i>Eriogonum</i> spp., <i>Erodium</i> <i>cicutarium</i>, <i>Langloisia</i> <i>setosissima</i>, <i>Loeseliastrum</i> <i>schottii</i>, <i>Mentzelia</i> spp., <i>Pectocarya</i> spp., <i>Phacelia</i> spp., <i>Plantago</i> <i>ovata</i> var. <i>insularis</i>, <i>Pleuraphis</i> <i>rigida</i> or <i>Schismus</i> spp. Shrub cover is sparse if present including <i>Ambrosia</i> <i>dumosa</i>, <i>Atriplex</i> <i>hymenelytra</i>, <i>Cylindropuntia</i> <i>echinocarpa</i>, <i>Encelia</i> <i>farinosa</i>, <i>Krameria</i> <i>grayi</i>, <i>Larrea</i> <i>tridentata</i>, <i>Opuntia</i> <i>basilaris</i> or <i>Tidestromia</i> <i>oblongifolia</i>.  </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  The herb layer is sparse to intermittent, and the non-vascular (cryptogamic crust) layer is sparse to intermittent. The shrub layer is sparse. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li>Landscape typically with < 5% perennial cover and characterized by herbs such as <i>Chorizanthe rigida, Chorizanthe brevicornu, Chaenactis</i> spp., <i>Eriogonum</i> spp., and/or <i>Geraea canescens,</i> (Evens et al. 2014, VegCAMP and AIS 2013).</li>
		
		<li>Ground surface generally with < 2% absolute cover, including herbaceous taxa such as <i>Chamaesyce</i> spp., <i>Phacelia neglecta, Erodium texanum, </i> and <i>Gilia latifolia</i> (LaDoux et al. 2013).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Desert pavement, broad alluvial fans, and lower slopes in the desert. The ground surface is sandy and gravelly mixed alluvium, with various rocks and gravel along with interstitial fine sediments.  </div>
</div>

        
